Sentencas: Yttria-stabilised zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte films for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications have been prepared by reactive DC sputtering.
Titulo: Influence of pre- and post-heat treatment of anode substrates on the properties of DC-sputtered YSZ electrolyte films

Sentencas: The pore structure of the anode substrates was modified by sintering at different temperatures between 1300 and 1400 degreesC and the influence of this microstructure on the gastightness of the deposited films was studied.
Titulo: Influence of pre- and post-heat treatment of anode substrates on the properties of DC-sputtered YSZ electrolyte films

Sentencas: The characterisation of the microstructure includes measurements of electrical conductivity as well as determination of porosity by image analysis and mercury porosimetry.
Titulo: Influence of pre- and post-heat treatment of anode substrates on the properties of DC-sputtered YSZ electrolyte films

Sentencas: At sintering temperatures of 1380 and 1400 degreesC, the surface of the anode substrate, coated by an anode functional layer, was dense.
Titulo: Influence of pre- and post-heat treatment of anode substrates on the properties of DC-sputtered YSZ electrolyte films

Sentencas: The 5- to 8-mum-thick sputtered electrolyte films were annealed again to increase the gastightness.
Titulo: Influence of pre- and post-heat treatment of anode substrates on the properties of DC-sputtered YSZ electrolyte films

Sentencas: At an annealing temperature of 1360 degreesC, a He leakage rate of 8 x 10(-8) mbar l/cm(2) s was achieved.
Titulo: Influence of pre- and post-heat treatment of anode substrates on the properties of DC-sputtered YSZ electrolyte films
